 Port Elizabeth -  The Port Elizabeth office of the South African Weather Service says it again expects high temperatures and high discomfort levels in parts of the Eastern Cape on Tuesday. "As can be seen from the attached we are expecting high temperatures over the western half of the province with high discomfort levels along the coastal belt between Tsitsikamma and Port Edward," said Garth Sampson, the SA Weather Service's Client Liaison Officer for the Eastern Cape. "It is for this reason that we HIGHLY RECOMMEND that all SCHOOL SPORT BE CANCELED TODAY "The calculated discomfort index for Port Elizabeth will be about 105 from midday." Sampson said that there will be slight cooling from the west on Wednesday with showers and thundershowers from the afternoon onwards. "Significant cooling is expected from Thursday with rainy cooler rainy conditions expected," he described. "These conditions will clear from the west on Saturday." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  